# Nexus UI layout and mobile behavior

## Files

- Shell and tabs: `components/NexusUI.jsx`
- Global styles / mobile overrides: `app/globals.css`

## Overflow and text

- Avoid horizontal scroll on the main chat column; only code blocks (`pre`) scroll horizontally inside bubbles.
- Use `min-width: 0` on flex children that hold long text so they shrink instead of forcing overflow.
- Markdown / prose: `overflow-wrap: break-word` (or equivalent) so long URLs and tokens do not spill off-screen.

## Chat panel

- Messages area: `flex: 1`, `min-height: 0`, vertical scroll only — do not use a large fixed `min-height` on the scroll region unless there is a documented reason.
- Prefer skipping `scrollIntoView` when `document.activeElement` is an `input` or `textarea` so mobile focus is not fighting auto-scroll.

## Primary navigation (tab bar)

- All main-panel tabs (Chat, Knowledge, Modes, Profile, Journal) must stay reachable on narrow widths: horizontal scroll on the tab row (`overflow-x: auto`, `flex-wrap: nowrap`, non-shrinking tab buttons). Sidebar thread list may stay behind the hamburger on mobile.
- Wrap the **logo row + tab strip** in **`.nexus-main-chrome`** (`position: sticky; top: 0`) so that chrome stays visible when the page or a parent scrolls; panel bodies scroll below it.

## Mobile touch / keyboard

- Full-viewport `fixed` layers (modals, sidebar overlay) must only be mounted when intended; verify with remote inspector if taps never reach inputs.
- On small viewports, the off-canvas sidebar (`transform` off-screen) must not steal taps: `pointer-events: none` when closed; **also** keep closed sidebar **`z-index: 0`** and **`.nexus-main` `z-index: 2`** so standalone WebViews deliver taps to the main panel (not a stale fixed layer). Open sidebar uses **`z-index: 100`**.
- Mobile: apply **`font-size: 16px`** and **`touch-action: manipulation`** to **all** `.nexus-main` / `.nexus-sidebar` inputs and textareas (not only chat/dump classes).
- Avoid `disabled` on the primary chat field when you still want focus/keyboard cues; prefer `readOnly` during streaming/save flows and disable **submit** instead, unless you intentionally block all interaction.

## Journal editor

- `react-simple-code-editor` stacks a `pre` and a positioned `textarea`. If focus fails on touch devices, ensure the textarea stacks above highlights (e.g. `z-index` on `.nexus-journal-editor-input`).
